    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-05-17T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-05-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="69"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d69">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15/963</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Belgium</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-05-17">May 17,
                            1929</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 227</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: On May 9, the French Ambassador called to express
                    his Government’s appreciation of your sympathetic attitude with regard to the
                    question of naval armaments, as set forth at the recent session of the
                    Preparatory Commission for the Disarmament Conference. He asked me what steps we
                    would take in the future and, in particular, whether we intended to call a new
                    Conference in this or the following year.</p>
                <p>I told him that we had made no definite plans as yet, but desired to bring to
                    fruition, as soon as the opportunity presented by your initiative would warrant,
                    the hope of President Hoover that a reduction in naval armaments might be
                    achieved.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">H. L. Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
